1776006849s:8595:"<h1 id="bkmrk-github-basics-guide">GitHub Basics Guide</h1>
<p id="bkmrk-a-beginner-friendly-">A beginner-friendly reference for using GitHub day to day.</p>
<hr id="bkmrk-">
<h2 id="bkmrk-what-is-github%3F">What Is GitHub?</h2>
<p id="bkmrk-git-is-a-version-con"><strong>Git</strong> is a version control system that tracks changes to your files over time.<br>
<strong>GitHub</strong> is a cloud-based platform that hosts Git repositories so you can collaborate, back up, and share your code.</p>
<hr id="bkmrk--1">
<h2 id="bkmrk-key-concepts">Key Concepts</h2>
<table id="bkmrk-term-what-it-means-r">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Term</th>
<th>What It Means</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Repository (Repo)</strong></td>
<td>A project folder tracked by Git</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Clone</strong></td>
<td>Download a copy of a repo to your machine</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Branch</strong></td>
<td>An isolated copy of the code to work in safely</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Commit</strong></td>
<td>A saved snapshot of your changes</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Push</strong></td>
<td>Upload your commits to GitHub</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Pull</strong></td>
<td>Download the latest changes from GitHub</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Pull Request (PR)</strong></td>
<td>A request to merge your branch into another branch</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Merge</strong></td>
<td>Combining one branch into another</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Fork</strong></td>
<td>Your own personal copy of someone else's repo</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr id="bkmrk--2">
<h2 id="bkmrk-setting-up-git-%28one-">Setting Up Git (One Time)</h2>
<pre id="bkmrk-%23-set-your-identity-"><code class="language-bash"># Set your identity
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "you@example.com"

# Verify your settings
git config --list
</code></pre>
<hr id="bkmrk--3">
<h2 id="bkmrk-starting-a-project">Starting a Project</h2>
<h3 id="bkmrk-option-a-%E2%80%94-create-a-">Option A — Create a new repo locally</h3>
<pre id="bkmrk-mkdir-my-project-cd-"><code class="language-bash">mkdir my-project
cd my-project
git init
</code></pre>
<h3 id="bkmrk-option-b-%E2%80%94-clone-an-">Option B — Clone an existing repo from GitHub</h3>
<pre id="bkmrk-git-clone-https%3A%2F%2Fgi"><code class="language-bash">git clone https://github.com/username/repo-name.git
cd repo-name
</code></pre>
<hr id="bkmrk--4">
<h2 id="bkmrk-the-basic-daily-work">The Basic Daily Workflow</h2>
<p id="bkmrk-this-is-the-loop-you">This is the loop you will use every single day:</p>
<pre id="bkmrk-pull-%E2%86%92-make-changes-"><code>Pull → Make Changes → Stage → Commit → Push
</code></pre>
<h3 id="bkmrk-1.-pull-the-latest-c">1. Pull the latest changes first</h3>
<pre id="bkmrk-git-pull-origin-main"><code class="language-bash">git pull origin main
</code></pre>
<h3 id="bkmrk-2.-make-your-changes">2. Make your changes</h3>
<p id="bkmrk-edit-your-files-in-a">Edit your files in any editor.</p>
<h3 id="bkmrk-3.-check-what-change">3. Check what changed</h3>
<pre id="bkmrk-git-status"><code class="language-bash">git status
</code></pre>
<h3 id="bkmrk-4.-stage-your-change">4. Stage your changes</h3>
<pre id="bkmrk-%23-stage-a-specific-f"><code class="language-bash"># Stage a specific file
git add filename.txt

# Stage everything at once
git add .
</code></pre>
<h3 id="bkmrk-5.-commit-your-chang">5. Commit your changes</h3>
<pre id="bkmrk-git-commit--m-%22brief"><code class="language-bash">git commit -m "Brief description of what you changed"
</code></pre>
<blockquote id="bkmrk-tip%3A-write-commit-me">
<p><strong>Tip:</strong> Write commit messages in plain English. Example: <code>"Fix login bug"</code> or <code>"Add README file"</code></p>
</blockquote>
<h3 id="bkmrk-6.-push-to-github">6. Push to GitHub</h3>
<pre id="bkmrk-git-push-origin-main"><code class="language-bash">git push origin main
</code></pre>
<hr id="bkmrk--5">
<h2 id="bkmrk-working-with-branche">Working with Branches</h2>
<p id="bkmrk-branches-let-you-wor">Branches let you work on features or fixes without affecting the main codebase.</p>
<pre id="bkmrk-%23-create-and-switch-"><code class="language-bash"># Create and switch to a new branch
git checkout -b feature/my-new-feature

# See all branches
git branch

# Switch between branches
git checkout main

# Push your branch to GitHub
git push origin feature/my-new-feature

# Merge a branch into main (do this locally or via Pull Request)
git checkout main
git merge feature/my-new-feature

# Delete a branch after merging
git branch -d feature/my-new-feature
</code></pre>
<hr id="bkmrk--6">
<h2 id="bkmrk-viewing-history">Viewing History</h2>
<pre id="bkmrk-%23-see-the-commit-his"><code class="language-bash"># See the commit history
git log

# Condensed one-line view
git log --oneline

# See what changed in a specific commit
git show &lt;commit-hash&gt;

# See unstaged changes in your files
git diff
</code></pre>
<hr id="bkmrk--7">
<h2 id="bkmrk-undoing-things">Undoing Things</h2>
<pre id="bkmrk-%23-undo-changes-to-a-"><code class="language-bash"># Undo changes to a file (before staging)
git restore filename.txt

# Unstage a file (keep changes, just un-add it)
git restore --staged filename.txt

# Undo the last commit (keep the changes in your files)
git reset --soft HEAD~1

# See a list of all recent HEAD positions (useful for recovery)
git reflog
</code></pre>
<blockquote id="bkmrk-warning%3A-avoid-git-r">
<p><strong>Warning:</strong> Avoid <code>git reset --hard</code> unless you are sure — it permanently discards changes.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr id="bkmrk--8">
<h2 id="bkmrk-pull-requests-%28prs%29">Pull Requests (PRs)</h2>
<p id="bkmrk-a-pull-request-is-ho">A Pull Request is how you propose merging your branch into <code>main</code> (or another branch) on GitHub.</p>
<ol id="bkmrk-push-your-branch-to-">
<li>Push your branch to GitHub</li>
<li>Go to the repo on github.com</li>
<li>Click <strong>"Compare &amp; pull request"</strong></li>
<li>Add a title and description</li>
<li>Click <strong>"Create pull request"</strong></li>
<li>A teammate reviews and approves it</li>
<li>Click <strong>"Merge pull request"</strong></li>
</ol>
<hr id="bkmrk--9">
<h2 id="bkmrk-common-issues-%26-fixe">Common Issues &amp; Fixes</h2>
<h3 id="bkmrk-merge-conflict">Merge Conflict</h3>
<p id="bkmrk-happens-when-two-peo">Happens when two people edited the same part of a file.</p>
<pre id="bkmrk-%23-after-a-failed-mer"><code class="language-bash"># After a failed merge, open the conflicted file and look for:
&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt; HEAD
your changes
=======
their changes
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; branch-name

# Edit the file to keep what you want, then:
git add filename.txt
git commit -m "Resolve merge conflict"
</code></pre>
<h3 id="bkmrk-wrong-branch">Wrong Branch</h3>
<pre id="bkmrk-%23-stash-your-work%2C-s"><code class="language-bash"># Stash your work, switch branches, then pop it back
git stash
git checkout correct-branch
git stash pop
</code></pre>
<h3 id="bkmrk-forgot-to-pull-befor">Forgot to Pull Before Working</h3>
<pre id="bkmrk-git-pull---rebase-or"><code class="language-bash">git pull --rebase origin main
</code></pre>
<hr id="bkmrk--10">
<h2 id="bkmrk-quick-reference-chea">Quick Reference Cheat Sheet</h2>
<pre id="bkmrk-git-clone-%3Curl%3E-%23-do"><code class="language-bash">git clone &lt;url&gt;           # Download a repo
git status                # See what's changed
git add .                 # Stage all changes
git commit -m "message"   # Save a snapshot
git push origin main      # Upload to GitHub
git pull origin main      # Download latest changes
git checkout -b &lt;branch&gt;  # Create + switch to new branch
git log --oneline         # See commit history
git diff                  # See unstaged changes
</code></pre>
